# StoaGraph (github.com/scanset/stoagraph)
#
# EVERYTHING IN THIS REPO IS RELEASABLE. There is no open/commercial split: the gate, the
# orchestrator, both consoles, the examples and the recipe library all ship. The ONLY things
# excluded below are (1) secrets, (2) regenerable runtime state, and (3) build artifacts.
#
# Nothing here may exclude source. Note the trap this file already fell into once: a pattern like
# `/stoa-kernel/harness` (meant for a compiled binary) also matches `stoa-kernel/harness/` — the
# ORCHESTRATOR'S SOURCE DIRECTORY — and silently swallowed 19 .go files. Never add a bare binary
# name that collides with a source dir. Build to bin/ instead.

# --- 1. secrets (NEVER commit) ---
# Provider API keys for the orchestrator's models. The gate holds none; only the orchestrator does.
models.json
# Control-plane role tokens (admin / approve / dispatch / operator) — generated 0600 on first start.
control.tokens
*.tokens
# The ed25519 key that signs approval releases.
approval.key
*.key
!*.pub.key
.env
.env.local

# --- 2. runtime state (regenerated; belongs in a volume, not in git) ---
/data/
/logs/
*.db
*.sqlite
*.jsonl

# --- 3. build artifacts ---
# Binaries go in bin/ (`go build -o bin/ ./cmd/...`), so no bare names can collide with source dirs.
/stoa-kernel/bin/
dist/
node_modules/
.next/
out/
*.tsbuildinfo

.DS_Store

# tool cache (syft etc.)
/.cache/
